contentrichtext.text: {{Italic title prefixed|3}} Two ships of the United States Navy have been named "Semmes", in honor of Commander (USN), Rear Admiral (CSN), Brigadier General (CSA) [[Raphael Semmes]] * {{USS|Semmes|DD-189}}, a [[Clemson class destroyer|''Clemson''-class]] [[destroyer]], commissioned in 1920, served in [[World War II]] and decommissioned in 1946. She was reclassified as AG-24 in 1935. * {{USS|Semmes|DDG-18}}, [[Charles F. Adams class destroyer|''Charles F. Adams''-class]] guided missile armed [[destroyer]], commissioned in 1962 and decommissioned in 1991. {{Shipindex}} {{DEFAULTSORT:Semmes}} [[Category:United States Navy ship names]]
